ary player and edwin moses before joining newsweek in 2007 freedman spent eight years at forbes magazine as a reporter foreign correspondent and europe bureau chief where he covered international business and a broad range of political legal and economic topics he has reported from europe asia and the middle east and written for the digital and or print editions of many other publications including the wall street journal and the atlantic freedman's work has been cited in congressional testimony excerpted in text books and acknowledged for its influence on public policy he has taught undergraduate writing and journalism a new york native freedman is a graduate of the university of illinois msj 1996 and emory university ba 1994 he is a member term of the council on foreign relations and has represented forbes and newsweek as a speaker or participant at executive conferences the world economic forum in davos switzerland and on television and radio programs including on the bbc and cnn publications cover can we unlearn the bomb michael freedman the atlantic 2011 html+ pdf+ search fsi search within everything courses events fellowships news op eds people publications research other pages recent commentary michael freedman can we unlearn the bomb cisac fsi stanford in the news the atlantic on may 6 2011 news around the web can we unlearn the bomb earlier this spring i visited the most nuclear bombed place in the world to get there i traveled one afternoon with a group of stanford university colleagues to las vegas and early the next morning made my way past the one armed may 6 2011 in the atlantic support map & directions contact rss+ rss xml feeds freeman spogli institute for international studies encina hall 616 serra st stanford ca 94305 6055 tel 650 723 4581 fax 650 725 2592 mail code 6055
